net.proteusframework.processes.form.registration

Class FormElementRegistration<T extends ComponentFactory>

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.processes.form.registration.FormElementRegistration<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the component factory type.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    NamedObject
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AddressFormRegistration, AddressPartRegistration, BirthdateFormRegistration, CaptchaRegistration, ContactOrganizationFormRegistration, DecisionButtonRegistration, EmailFormRegistration, ExtraValueRegistration, GenderFormRegistration, HTMLTextRegistration, LocaleChooserRegistration, LoginCredentialRegistration, MetaDataRegistration, NamePartRegistration, PhoneNumberFormRegistration, PrincipalRoleSubsetRegistration, PrincipalStatusRegistration, ReportViewRegistration, ScriptRegistration, SubmitButtonRegistration, SummaryRegistration

    public abstract class FormElementRegistration<T extends ComponentFactory>
extends Object
implements NamedObject
    Registers a ComponentFactory implementation with the intent of being used in a FormEditor. Implementations provide classification information, and view/edit UI components for a Form Element.

    Implementations should register themselves as spring beans either through annotations or in a spring bean XML file like cmsComponentFactory.spring.xml.

    Author:
    Pat Double (double@i2rd.com)
